🟢 Why JSON kaadu?

Spring Boot rule simple:

Return Type	Response Format
String	Plain text
Object	JSON
List<Object>	JSON Array
🧪 Example 1 – String
@GetMapping("/hello")
public String hello(){
    return "Hello";
}

Response:

Hello

Not JSON.

🧪 Example 2 – Object
@GetMapping("/student")
public Student getStudent(){
    return new Student(1,"Hemanth","Spring");
}

Response:

{
"id":1,
"name":"Hemanth",
"course":"Spring"
}
🧪 Example 3 – List
@GetMapping("/students")
public List<Student> getStudents(){
    return List.of(
        new Student(1,"Hemanth","Spring"),
        new Student(2,"Ravi","Java")
    );
}

Response:

[
 {
  "id":1,
  "name":"Hemanth",
  "course":"Spring"
 },
 {
  "id":2,
  "name":"Ravi",
  "course":"Java"
 }
]
🧠 Why JSON object vachindi earlier?

Because method return type:

Student

Spring Boot internally:

Student object → JSON

convert chesindi using Jackson.

